{
  "text": "In line with the IUCN SPSC (2017) recommendation to 'assume an average area occupied by a mature individual and estimate the number of mature individuals from the area covered by the taxon', the Swedish Red List Committee for Bryophytes interpreted 'mature individual' in a pragmatic way by using the concept of an 'individual-equivalent' [CITATION_1] . This is closely related to the concept of the 'functional individual' in fungal species [CITATION_2] . Thus, in the European Bryophyte Red List, we applied the following definitions:",
